Package: reintervals
Title: Confidence, Prediction, Tolerance, and New-Group-Mean Intervals for
    Linear Mixed Models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Perceval", "Sondag", email = "reintervals@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0001-9183-6991"))
Description: Confidence, prediction, tolerance, and new-group-mean (also
    called CInew or new-batch-mean) intervals for linear mixed models fitted
    with 'lme4' ('lmerMod' objects), returned through one uniform interface.
    Several validated interval engines are provided and selected automatically
    for the fitted model, with a manual override: an expected-mean-square,
    modified large-sample construction for random-intercept models (Francq,
    Lin and Hoyer (2019) <doi:10.1002/sim.8386>); a restricted-maximum-
    likelihood closed form for random-slope models; an unweighted lot-mean
    analysis-of-variance closed form for unbalanced single-observation
    fixed-slope stability designs (Montes, Burdick and Leblond (2019)
    <doi:10.5731/pdajpst.2018.008839>); and a generalized-pivotal-quantity
    Monte Carlo engine (Oliva-Aviles and Hauser (2025)
    <doi:10.1080/00401706.2024.2407324>). General fixed effects are supported for random-intercept models;
    random-slope models are supported for a single time covariate (the
    stability design). The methods serve general linear-mixed-model interval
    estimation, with particular support for pharmaceutical stability and
    shelf-life work and for bioassay applications through the tolerance and
    new-group-mean intervals.
